The young impling jar is the result of successfully catching a Young impling, whilst also having an empty impling jar. Young impling jars are not that commonly looted because of the low value of the loot. Instead, the jar can be traded in singularly to Elnock Inquisitor for 3 empty impling jars. This allows the player to collect 3 more higher level implings for them to loot.

If a player catches an impling without an empty impling jar, they will automatically receive the loot instead.

You can trade two of this jar, along with three baby impling jars and one Gourmet impling jar to Elnock for a vial of Imp repellent.

Loot[edit | edit source]

At current Grand Exchange prices, opening a young impling jar gives 956 worth of loot, on average. This means opening young impling jars marks an average profit of −1,930 per jar, however this does not include loot from clue scrolls.

On average, one would profit −96,497 to get an easy clue scroll, and −48,249 to get a beginner clue scroll from young impling jars at current Grand Exchange prices, excluding the rewards from the completed Treasure Trails.

The following drop rates are provided by Jagex, unless otherwise specified.

Impling jar[edit | edit source]

An empty impling jar is returned when removing the loot, with a 10% chance of it breaking.[1]
